for this is well pleaſing to the Lord: It will be for their preſent, as well as future welfare. The wiſe man ſaith, My ſon hear the inſtruction of thy father, and forſake not the law of thy mother, for they ſhall be an ornament of grace unto thy head, and chains about thy neck. The 〈◊〉 of obedience is better than all burnt-off 〈…〉 . The Lord ſaith of the houſe 〈…〉
Becauſe ye have obeyed the commandment of Jonadab, your father, and kept all his precepts, and done according unto all that he hath commanded you: Therefore, thus ſaith the Lord of hoſts, the God of Iſrael, Jonadab, the ſon of Rechab, ſhall not want a man to ſtand before me for ever.
